Output Parser for PIDC

pidc.Rd

This function parses the standard output generated by the BEELINE tool PIDC.

pidc(file_path)

Arguments

file_path

a file path to the PIDC output file generated by BEELINE.

Author

Sergio Vasquez and Hajk-Georg Drost

Examples

# path to PIDC output file
pidc_output <- system.file('beeline_examples/PIDC/outFile.txt', package = 'edgynode')
# import PIDC specific output
pidc_parsed <- pidc(pidc_output)

#> Repairing names...
#> New names:

#> * `` -> ...2

#> * `` -> ...5
